<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="360" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1076,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1292,1318]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Park, 2020" authorityName="Park" authorityYear="2020" box="[664,909,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Thubdora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirinae">
<emphasis box="[664,779,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">T. mirinae</emphasis>
Park, 2020
</taxonomicName>
with small costal patch on the forewing, but it can be distinguished by the much smaller size (
<quantity box="[692,773,1328,1355]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Park" authorityYear="2020" box="[811,927,1329,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Thubdora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirinae">
<emphasis box="[811,927,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">T. mirinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the male genitalia with the uncus more broadened, the valva strongly upturned, the juxta larger, and tergite VIII concave on caudal margin with shorter stalk. It is a bit similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Park &amp; Karisch, 2021" authorityName="Park &amp; Karisch" authorityYear="2021" box="[446,870,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Thubdora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernaculella">
<emphasis box="[446,614,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">T. vernaculella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; Karisch, T." box="[623,870,1400,1426]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" pagination="581 - 593" refId="ref10153" refString="Park, K. - T. &amp; Karisch, T. (2021) Lecithoceridae (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea) of Bioko Island, with description of two new species (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea, Lecithoceridae). Zootaxa, 4995 (3), 581 - 593. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4995.3.12" type="journal article" year="2021">Park &amp; Karisch, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which was described from Bioko, but can be distinguished by having a more distinct orange-white costal patch on the forewing, and the male genitalia with the uncus more broadened distally, the gnathos much smaller, the valva less elongated, and the aedeagus with bundles of bush-like spines medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="362" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1076,2038]" box="[199,820,1544,1571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1544,1570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<figureCitation box="[424,560,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[166,1412,385,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-104@4.[151,1436,381,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thubdora ivoryensis Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Male, holotype; A1, Labial palpus; A2, Label; B, Male genitalia, GU-3887/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Abdomen; D, Female genitalia, GU-3891/Karisch, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810514/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Figs. 3A–A</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[560,574,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,600,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-247@2.[151,1436,597,1813]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A: View from Mt. Tonkoui over the anthropogenic influenced tropical rain forest on the slopes (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997); B: Collecting site for light trapping with altimontane rain forest fragments at the South-Eastern slopes of Mt. Tonkoui (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997; C: Fragmentary secondary rain forest south of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 20 viii 1997); D: Collecting site at the Southern border of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 17 viii 1997)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810510/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">2</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[712,815,1544,1571]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="3" pageNumber="360" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1076,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Head</emphasis>
: Shiny dark brown, with yellowish orange erect scales laterally. Antenna slightly shorter than forewing; scape elongated, broadened distally; flagellum yellowish-orange, with brownish annulations, finely serrated. Second palpomere of labial palpus thickened, arched, dark brown on outer surface, paler on inner surface; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1299,1313,1652,1666]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">rd</superScript>
palpomere slender, strongly upturned, as long as 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[589,605,1688,1702]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">nd</superScript>
palpomere, dark brown on outer surface, light yellow dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1076,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Thorax</emphasis>
: Shiny dark brown; tegulae same color. Hind tibia roughly scaled, shiny blackish gray with yellowish bands medially and apically. Forewing ground color shiny dark brown with a copper lustre; antemedian fascia broad often obscure, tarnished black; costa slightly arched in basal third, with a small, wedge-shaped orange-white costal patch at 4/5; apex obtuse, slightly produced; termen oblique; fringe concolorous with ground color, with a narrow yellowish white basal line. Hind wing ground color pale grayish brown; apex produced; fringe concolorous, with a narrow yellowish-white basal line.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1076,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[320,408,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[166,1412,385,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-104@4.[151,1436,381,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thubdora ivoryensis Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Male, holotype; A1, Labial palpus; A2, Label; B, Male genitalia, GU-3887/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Abdomen; D, Female genitalia, GU-3891/Karisch, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810514/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="360">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
): Dark brown dorsally; subgenital segments mixed with orange gray. Spinose zones broadly developed, narrowed beyond sternite VII; tergite VIII with large crescent sclerite, deeply concave on caudal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis box="[199,363,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[378,510,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[166,1412,385,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-104@4.[151,1436,381,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thubdora ivoryensis Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Male, holotype; A1, Labial palpus; A2, Label; B, Male genitalia, GU-3887/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Abdomen; D, Female genitalia, GU-3891/Karisch, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810514/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">Figs. 3B, B</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[510,521,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-101@1.[151,1436,345,1276]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Topographical map of the region Northwest of Man, Black circles = collecting sites; inserted map: Ivory Coast with marked collecting area (arrow) (Openstreetmap, inserted map: Mapsland, CCA 3.0)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810508/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">1</figureCitation>
): Uncus broadened apically, slightly emarginated medially. Basal plate of gnathos with rounded caudal margin, exceeding apex of uncus; median process rather small. Valva elongated; costa expanded anteriorly in basal 1/3; cucullus strongly upturned, densely setose, with gently arched ventral margin; apex rounded. Juxta large, with quadrate median plate and large, triangular membranous plates latero-caudally. Aedeagus as long as valva, slightly narrowed toward apex; cornuti consisting of bundles of various setae-like shapes beyond half.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810514" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6810514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810514/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="361" startId="4.[151,250,1928,1952]" targetBox="[166,1412,385,1886]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1928,1989]" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1928,1952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Park &amp; Karisch" authorityName="Park &amp; Karisch" authorityYear="2022" box="[280,654,1928,1953]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Thubdora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ivoryensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[280,489,1928,1952]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="361">Thubdora ivoryensis</emphasis>
Park &amp; Karisch
</taxonomicName>
, 
